                            <comment id="14072071" author="jdcryans" created="Wed, 23 Jul 2014 18:16:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A few little things:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;+    &amp;lt;para&amp;gt;Apache HBase (TM) provides a replication mechanism to copy data between HBase
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We needed to put the whole Apache HBase (TM) here because we were mentioning HBase for the first time, but now that it&apos;s in the middle of the documentation we can just replace this by just &quot;HBase provides a replication...&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;+    &amp;lt;procedure&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s not a procedure, it&apos;s more a description of what happens when you replicate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;+      &amp;lt;title&amp;gt;Replication FAQ&amp;lt;/title&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can remove the whole section, it&apos;s stale and nobody&apos;s been asking those questions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Finally, we could use a few more &quot;xml:id&quot; tags, at least for the first level below replication.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14075826" author="misty" created="Mon, 28 Jul 2014 01:31:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jdcryans&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jdcryans&quot;&gt;Jean-Daniel Cryans&lt;/a&gt;. I fixed up the trademark thing and removed the FAQ. I changed the markup of the procedure to a couple of orderedlists. I reorganized some of the other sub-sections into &amp;lt;section&amp;gt;s for easy linking later, even though I don&apos;t like to see sections nested so deep. I did not add any xml:ids because they are a pain to maintain so you should add them as needed. Just add an ID as you need to link to it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
